<br>
If you have to weight rolls based on their level (which I DON'T agree with), why not weight the actual rolls rather than giving more rolls out?<br>
<br>
Randoms will be /ran (10 x LVL) 1000<br>
So a level 50 will /ran 500 1000<br>
Level 60 /ran 600 1000<br>
Level 65 /ran 650 1000<br>
<br>
That way you can award bonus weight for other things.  For example... usable classes could get a 100 point bonus (more likely that an item will go to a player who can, um, USE it).  Players who stay longer get bonuses (25 points per hour, maybe).  Of course, you can play with the /random values so you don't get someone rolling /ran 900 1000, but you get the idea.  For simplicity's sake, just do the level part.<br>
<br>
